- This document does not contain stack, database, component, or implementation details
- A reader should understand what the project does without reading code

## 9.1 Common Mistakes

Wrong:

- "Use React + PostgreSQL + Redis to build an admin system."
- "Create three tables first, then implement login APIs."

Why it is wrong:

- That already describes implementation and execution order instead of delivery goals.

Better:

- "Users can log in and see the status of their tasks."
- "The system can create, view, and update core records with clear feedback."

